org.mindswap.owls.grounding
Interface Grounding<A extends AtomicGrounding<T>,T>

All Superinterfaces:
OWLEntity, OWLIndividual, OWLObject, OWLValue
All Known Subinterfaces:
JavaGrounding, UPnPGrounding, WSDLGrounding
All Known Implementing Classes:
GroundingImpl, JavaGroundingImpl, UPnPGroundingImpl, WSDLGroundingImpl
public interface Grounding<A extends AtomicGrounding<T>,T>
extends OWLIndividual

Represents the grounding that some Service supports.

As of OWL-S 1.2 the corresponding concept in the OWL-S ontology is Grounding

getAtomicGrounding

A getAtomicGrounding(AtomicProcess process)
Get the atomic process grounding defined for the given atomic process. If there are multiple groundings specified one of them is selected arbitrarily. Consider to use getAtomicGroundings(AtomicProcess) instead.

Parameters:
process - The atomic process for which to get its atomic process grounding defined in this grounding.
Returns:
The atomic process grounding, or null if none is specified for the given process.

Returns:
The list of atomic process groundings.

removeAtomicGroundings

void removeAtomicGroundings(AtomicProcess process)
Removes the atomic groundings for the given atomic process from this grounding by removing the corresponding statements, e.g., OWLS.Grounding#hasAtomicProcessGrounding for WSDL groundings. The atomic groundings itself are not changed at all.

Parameters:
process - The atomic process to which the removable atomic groundings are bound.

removeAtomicGrounding

void removeAtomicGrounding(A apg)
Removes the atomic grounding from this grounding by removing the corresponding statement, e.g., OWLS.Grounding#hasAtomicProcessGrounding for WSDL groundings. The atomic grounding itself is not changed at all.

Parameters:
apg - The atomic process grounding to be removed.

removeAtomicGroundings

void removeAtomicGroundings()
Removes all atomic groundings from this grounding by removing the the corresponding statements, e.g., OWLS.Grounding#hasAtomicProcessGrounding for WSDL groundings. The atomic groundings itself are not changed at all.
